history.content:
I need a couple of sharp students to build a control system to let a large

quadcopter launch a bunch of small quadcopters and control them autonomously.

The mothership, something like a DJI Phantom or Inspire, will have a magazine of perhaps a dozen 

cheap little quads like CX-10s.  The Phantom will use the existing radio control in the CX-10s

to fly them using its own camera for location feedback.

Send me an email if you're interested.

As before, if you can't find my email, you're not qualified. :)
history.subject: Research now: drones launching drones
